  "body": "These are the suggestions for the top of the left column of the HomeTab.  \r\nDon't begin work on this until we have one more meeting about this.  \r\nThis story of Issues will have a graphic comp to show what it should look like.\r\n\r\n- [ ] Remove the outlined logo: \r\n<img width=\"92\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6050001/208997087-9f115349-31c7-4e30-a4c9-4b0b3ca6caad.png\">\r\n\r\n- [ ] Change  The Native IDE for Web3 Development.   to **The Web3 Dev Environment**  (and it does not need a period (.) at the end.\r\n- [ ] The current naviation on the HomeTab is : [Website](https://remix-project.org/)    [Documentation](https://remix-ide.readthedocs.io/en/latest)     [Remix Plugin](https://remix-plugin-docs.readthedocs.io/en/latest/)    [Remix Desktop](https://github.com/ethereum/remix-desktop/releases)    \r\nChange the text of the link **Website** to  About Us. Keep  Documentation and remove Remix Plugin & Desktop.\r\n- [ ] Remove the Files title (its a label in HTML)\r\n- [ ] Change the button New File to **New Workspace** and also change the functionality to make a new workspace - so that the modal comes up.\r\n- [ ] Remove the Open File button\r\n- [ ] Add a label called Connect.  Below it will be a switch\r\nBrowser Storage      **switch**    Local Filesystem\r\nThis will both display the status of the connection and will prompt a change.\r\n- If the user is on browser storage and switches to Local Filesystem, the remixd modal will come up and if then connection goes through, the switch will stay on the Local Filesystem side.  If the connection to remixd fails then the switch would flop back to the Browser Storage side.\r\n- if connected to Local Filesystem and the user drags the slider back to browser storage, then the last used filesystem would be loaded.  It would be the same behavior as if the user closes Remixd in the terminal.\r\n\r\n- [ ] Load From section - add a button to Clone. This should be the 1st button.\r\n\r\n",
